social_posts.post_text: This Sunday at 5pm pt is the last update of the year 🤗 I’ll be making as many pieces as I can before then so let me know your requests ♥️🎄🫶

Happy December! Our advent calendar is up and filled with family activities (and a few sweets too, of course 😉 🍫). Some of our favorites are doing a Christmas craft, hot cocoa + Christmas lights.. and my favorite- making Christmas cookies 🍪
2 more days till the last shop update of the year! 💝🤗 How cute is the Dreamland Ornament Set tied onto these garlands?! 🤩

The girls and I each have a different favorite way to make snowflakes and I just love seeing them now all over our home 🤗❄️ I’ve saved diys for the paper bag and doily snowflakes in highlights in case you want to make them too 🤍

This season has flown by and I already miss making all the very merry goodies 💫 These tassel pom sets were my fave to make and if you missed them don’t worry… as long as I have the materials, they are available to order when I open back custom orders in January ♥️
Are you all done wrapping? I ran out of gift boxes and had to brave the crowd at Target over the weekend.. TWICE lol 😆 but now I’m allmmoost done 💝

Lol this guy 🤣 He’s not one of my favorite traditions… but he can be a lot of fun ♥️ Also, I’m pretty proud of him for NOT forgetting to check in with Santa a single night this year 🥳 …but there are a still few more days left 🤪

It’s just me saying thank youuuu and in my feels 🫶 I can’t believe August marked 6 years since the shop’s very first sale 😱 My weaving style has come a looong way since that very first sale on an Etsy shop that I named using my girls’ nicknames 😆🧡 Swipe to see that very first weaving I sold in my early days that I oh so carefully and lovingly wrapped while thanking God that there was at least one person out there that likes my art (besides my family lol) 🫠🤗

Had to share this custom order I just finished because it’s too sweet not to 🌸🤍🐚 I take custom orders most of the year, but stop taking them once I start getting into holiday making (which is now ) because life usually gets too coo coo crazy for me lol 🤪

It’s finally October, but “Skelly Mama” has been out of the garage for about a couple weeks now lol. I’ve been sharing all the fun in stories and thought I’d pop it on the feed for good time memories 😆 I move her around while the girls are at school and during the weekend, Leighton (our youngest and earliest riser haha) likes to do the honors 🧡
When you’re making Christmas goodies, but Halloween is still on your mind 💜

Making content annnnd making pieces for the shop has been errr… challenging lol… so keeping this reel prreeettty simple haha 😛 But I am still making holiday goodies friends… I share more in stories than on the feed, but I’m still around… thus is the life of this juggling mama 😆🩷☺️

✨Shop Update is this Thursday at 5pm pst friends! ✨ annnnd it might be the last update of the year for moi. It’s always been a challenge finding time to make and time to be present during the holiday season… I thought it would get easier as the girls got older, but now that they are on their own paths of interests and hobbies and friends.. the time for being present feels even more important to me 🥹🩷🫶
Tis the season for making… and drinking all the hot drinks in cutie patootie mugs ☕️🩷 Thanks friends for all the love on my last update of the year 🥳

Raise your hand if your tree is up 🙋🏻‍♀️😆 I’m not trying to skip Thanksgiving because it’s always been one of my favorite holidays (good food, convo, and company is my love language) so - thankful for this house that I’m slowly making our home -  home to our family of homebodies 🫶 - and for all the little things here that make me smile 😊 Hope you all have a Happy Thanksgiving 🍁
🤎 Happy Thanksgiving from our fam to yours 🧡

Grateful for you and this blessed life ♥️🥳

My bad.. totally forgot to post that everything is 30% off in the shop 🙈 Today is the last day, but it’s been going on all weekend lol (got caught up in all the weekend craft making festivities) 😅 No code needed for the discount ♥️
